<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:31PM CDT until June 16 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1000 PM CDT
FOR ETOWAH AND NORTHERN ST. CLAIR COUNTIES...
At 931 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Gadsden to 6 miles south of Ashville, moving west
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Gadsden, Rainbow City, Attalla, Hokes Bluff, Springville, Glencoe,
Ashville, Sardis City, Ragland, Steele, Altoona, Walnut Grove, Reece
City, Tabor Road, Aurora, Ballplay, Gadsden Mall, Noccalula Falls,
Neely Henry Lake and Southside.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
